consensus_statement:
My strategy would be to first spend time with my fellow commissioner to:
•	ensure that we all understand the laws, rules, and procedures that we must adhere to;
•	understand the perspective, goals, and aspirations of my fellow commissioners; and;
•	Agree on a set of aspirational goals that we share as commissioners that we can refer back to when we find ourselves attempting to resolve the eventual differences of opinion that will arise.
In these times where we see and experience many examples of uncivil actions in our public and private arenas, it is critical that we focus first on what we can agree on so that we have touchstones that we can revisit when we have subsequent disagreements.  
These boards must aspire to be examples of civility, creativity, and action so that we can deliver a result to the people of Colorado that enable our citizens to engage meaningfully on the issues, policies, and candidates that we will encounter over the next 10 years.

